### GET /admin/kyc/all

This endpoint retrieves all KYC (Know Your Customer) information for admin purposes.

#### Request

This is a GET request to the endpoint `{{baseUrl}}/admin/kyc/all`.

#### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "success": true,
  "msg": "",
  "kyc": {
    "userId": "",
    "profile": [
      {
        "storeId": "",
        "address": {
          "state": "",
          "city": "",
          "lga": "",
          "town": "",
          "street": "",
          "houseNo": "",
          "landMark": ""
        },
        "banner": {
          "id": "",
          "url": ""
        },
        "logo": {
          "id": "",
          "url": ""
        }
      }
    ],
    "bankDetails": [
      {
        "bankName": "",
        "accountNumber": "",
        "accountName": ""
      }
    ],
    "documents": [
      {
        "id": "",
        "url": "",
        "docId": "",
        "name": "",
        "status": ""
      }
    ],
    "store": [
      {
        "storeId": "",
        "name": "",
        "category": [
          {
            "_id": "",
            "id": "",
            "name": "",
            "description": "",
            "status": ""
          }
        ],
        "createdAt": "",
        "updatedAt": ""
      }
    ],
    "logistics": [],
    "onBoarded": true,
    "createdAt": "",
    "updatedAt": ""
  }
}

 ```

The response contains a `success` flag indicating the success status of the request, along with the `kyc` object containing various KYC information such as `profile`, `bankDetails`, `documents`, `store`, `logistics`, `onBoarded`, `createdAt`, and `updatedAt`.

