request.description:
### GET /user/notification/all

This endpoint retrieves all notifications for a user.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

#### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following properties:

- `success` (boolean): Indicates if the request was successful.

- `msg` (string): An optional message from the server.

- `notification` (array): An array containing notification objects with the following properties:
    - `id` (string): The unique identifier of the notification.

    - `userId` (string): The user ID associated with the notification.

    - `title` (string): The title of the notification.

    - `category` (string): The category of the notification.

    - `info` (string): Additional information related to the notification.

    - `createdAt` (string): The timestamp when the notification was created.

    - `updatedAt` (string): The timestamp when the notification was last updated.


#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "notification": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "userId": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "title": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "category": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "info": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "createdAt": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "updatedAt": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

