request.description:
# Chat Send

This endpoint is used to send a chat message to a specific receiver.

## Request

### Request Body

- receiver (string): The ID of the message receiver.

- message (string): The content of the message.


Example:

``` json
{
    "receiver": "GBXRC3VR3H",
    "message": "{{$randomLoremSentence}}"
}

 ```

## Response

- Status: 200

- Content Type: application/json


### Response Body (JSON Schema)

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "msg": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

The response contains a JSON object with the following properties:

- success (boolean): Indicates if the message was sent successfully.

- msg (string): Additional message or error details.


Example Response:

``` json
{
    "success": true,
    "msg": ""
}

 ```

### Update Chat Viewed Status

This endpoint allows the client to update the viewed status of a chat.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- Body:

    - id (text, required): The ID of the chat to be marked as viewed.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

- Status: 200 OK

- Content-Type: application/json


Example response body:

``` json
{
  "success": true,
  "msg": ""
}

 ```

### Delete Chat

This endpoint allows the client to delete a chat

#### Request

- Query Parameters:

    - id (required, string): The ID of the chat to be marked as viewed.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "success": {
    "type": "boolean"
  },
  "msg": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}

 ```

- Status: 200 OK

- Content-Type: application/json


Example response body:

``` json
{
  "success": true,
  "msg": ""
}

 ```

### POST /user/ticket

This endpoint is used to create a new ticket for the user.

#### Request Body

- title (string, required): The title of the ticket.

- description (string, required): The description of the ticket.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains a boolean field "success" indicating the success status of the request, and a string field "msg" which may contain additional information about the request execution.

### PATCH /user/ticket/close

This endpoint is used to update the status of a user ticket to "close".

#### Request

The request body should be in JSON format and include the following parameters:

- `id` (string): The unique identifier of the ticket to be closed.

- `status` (string): The new status of the ticket, which should be set to "close".


#### Response

The response will be in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response will include:

- `success` (boolean): Indicates whether the request was successful.

- `msg` (string): A message related to the request, if any.

### POST /user/ticket/chat

This endpoint is used to send a chat message for a specific ticket.

#### Request Body

- `ticketId` (string) - The ID of the ticket for which the message is being sent.

- `message` (string) - The content of the chat message.


#### Response

The response is a JSON object with the following properties:

- `success` (boolean) - Indicates whether the request was successful.

- `msg` (string) - An optional message from the server.


#### Example Response

``` json
{
    "success": true,
    "msg": ""
}

 ```

#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "msg": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Endpoint Description

This endpoint is used to endorse or like a specific Product, Store or Rider.

### Request

- Body:

    - prodId (string, optional): The ID of the product to be liked or unlike. or

    - storeId (string, optional): The ID of the store to be linked or unlike. or

    - riderId (string, optional): The ID of the rider to be liked or unlike.


### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "msg": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Update Endorsement Rating

This endpoint allows the client to update the rating for a specific product endorsement.

#### Request Body

- prodId (string, optional): The ID of the product to be rated. or

- storeId (string, optional): The ID of the store to be rated. or

- riderId (string, optional): The ID of the rider to be rated.

- rating (number, required): The new rating to be assigned to the product endorsement.


#### Response

The response is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### PUT /endorse/review

This endpoint is used to update a review for a specific store.

#### Request

The request should be made with a JSON payload in the raw request body type, including the following parameters:

- `storeId` (string): The ID of the store for which the review is being updated.(Optional)

- prodId (string): The ID of the product to be reviewed.(Optional).

- riderId (string): The ID of the Rider to be reviewd.(Optional).

- `review` (string): The updated review for the store.


#### Response

Upon a successful execution, the endpoint returns a JSON response with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "msg": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains the following keys:

- `success` (boolean): Indicates whether the update was successful.

- `msg` (string): An optional message related to the update.

